<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="sv">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Velocity – Week {{ week }}, {{ generated_at }}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.datatables.net/1.13.8/css/dataTables.bootstrap5.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.datatables.net/buttons/2.4.2/css/buttons.bootstrap5.min.css">
  <style>
    body { font-size: 0.9rem; }
    .badge-high  { background: #198754; color: #fff; }
    .badge-med   { background: #ffc107; color: #000; }
    .badge-low   { background: #dc3545; color: #fff; }
    .badge-dim   { background: #6c757d; color: #fff; }
    .channel-tradera { background: #cfe2ff; color: #084298; padding: 1px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 600; }
    .channel-vinted  { background: #f8d7da; color: #842029; padding: 1px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 600; }
    .delta-positive  { color: #198754; font-weight: 600; }
    .delta-negative  { color: #dc3545; font-weight: 600; }
    th { white-space: nowrap; }
    .stat-card { border-left: 4px solid #0d6efd; padding: .75rem 1rem; background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 4px; }
    .stat-card.tradera { border-left-color: #084298; }
    .stat-card.vinted  { border-left-color: #842029; }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-white">
<div class="container-fluid py-4 px-4">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-start mb-4">
    <div>
      <h2 class="mb-0">Velocity Report</h2>
      <small class="text-muted">Week {{ week }} · Generated {{ generated_at }} · 90-day rolling window</small>
    </div>
    <div class="d-flex gap-3">
      <div class="stat-card tradera text-center">
        <div class="fs-4 fw-bold">{{ total_tradera }}</div>
        <div class="text-muted" style="font-size:.75rem">Tradera (sold)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card vinted text-center">
        <div class="fs-4 fw-bold">{{ total_vinted }}</div>
        <div class="text-muted" style="font-size:.75rem">Vinted (active)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card text-center">
        <div class="fs-4 fw-bold">{{ brand_count }}</div>
        <div class="text-muted" style="font-size:.75rem">brands matched</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Pricing Calculator ── -->
  <style>
    /* Three-tier dropdown contrast */
    select option              { color: #212529; }                    /* normal: full visibility */
    select option.calc-low-data { color: #888; font-style: italic; }   /* 1–9 samples: dimmed */
    select option.calc-no-data  { color: #ccc; font-style: italic; }   /* 0 samples: very faded */

    .result-box { border-radius: 6px; padding: 1rem; margin-bottom: .5rem; position: relative; }
    .result-box.tradera { background: #cfe2ff; }
    .result-box.vinted  { background: #f8d7da; }
    .result-box.empty   { background: #f1f3f5; }
    .result-box.low-confidence { opacity: 0.85; border: 2px dashed #ffc107; }
    .result-box .price  { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; }
    .result-box .unit   { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 400; }
    .result-box .channel-tag { font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .04em; }
    .result-box .meta { font-size: .8rem; color: #555; margin-top: .25rem; }
    .result-box .gran { font-size: .7rem; color: #666; margin-top: .35rem; }
    .result-box .confidence-badge {
      position: absolute; top: .5rem; right: .75rem;
      font-size: .65rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px;
    }
    .result-box .confidence-badge.high { background: #198754; color: #fff; }
    .result-box .confidence-badge.low  { background: #ffc107; color: #000; }
  </style>

  <div class="card mb-5 border-0 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-header bg-success text-white d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between">
      <strong>Pricing Calculator</strong>
      <span class="text-light" style="font-size:.8rem">
        Cascading filters · grayed options have &lt; 10 samples
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="row g-2 mb-3">
        <div class="col-md-3">
          <label class="form-label small mb-1">Brand</label>
          <select class="form-select form-select-sm" id="calc-brand"></select>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-3">
          <label class="form-label small mb-1">Category</label>
          <select class="form-select form-select-sm" id="calc-category"></select>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-3">
          <label class="form-label small mb-1">Size</label>
          <select class="form-select form-select-sm" id="calc-size"></select>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-3">
          <label class="form-label small mb-1">Condition <small class="text-muted">(Vinted only)</small></label>
          <select class="form-select form-select-sm" id="calc-condition">
            <option value="">Any (no condition filter)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row g-3" id="calc-result">
        <div class="col-md-6"><div class="result-box empty" data-channel="tradera">Loading…</div></div>
        <div class="col-md-6"><div class="result-box empty" data-channel="vinted">Loading…</div></div>
      </div>

      <details class="mt-3">
        <summary class="text-muted" style="font-size:.8rem; cursor:pointer">How this works</summary>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2" style="font-size:.75rem">
          Pick brand → category → size → condition. Each dropdown shows what's available given prior choices,
          with sample sizes per channel <code>(T:tradera V:vinted)</code>. Options below the n≥10 threshold are grayed.
          The result panel shows both channels at once. If a cell has too few samples at the chosen specificity,
          the calculator falls back through coarser levels (brand×cat → brand-only → cat-only) and labels the match.
          Condition data is Vinted-only — for Tradera the condition field always falls through to condition-agnostic levels.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script type="application/json" id="pricing-lookups">{{ pricing_lookups_json | safe }}</script>
  <script type="application/json" id="cascade-data">{{ cascade_json | safe }}</script>
  <script>
  (function () {
    const lookups = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('pricing-lookups').textContent);
    const cascade = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('cascade-data').textContent);
    const MIN_N = cascade.min_n;

    const LEVELS = [
      { code: 'bcscZ', fields: ['brand','category','size','channel','condition'], label: 'brand × cat × size × channel × condition', needsCondition: true },
      { code: 'bccZ',  fields: ['brand','category','channel','condition'],         label: 'brand × cat × channel × condition',        needsCondition: true },
      { code: 'bchZ',  fields: ['brand','channel','condition'],                    label: 'brand × channel × condition',              needsCondition: true },
      { code: 'cscZ',  fields: ['category','size','channel','condition'],          label: 'cat × size × channel × condition',         needsCondition: true },
      { code: 'ccZ',   fields: ['category','channel','condition'],                 label: 'cat × channel × condition',                needsCondition: true },
      { code: 'bcsc',  fields: ['brand','category','size','channel'],              label: 'brand × cat × size × channel' },
      { code: 'bcc',   fields: ['brand','category','channel'],                     label: 'brand × cat × channel' },
      { code: 'bch',   fields: ['brand','channel'],                                label: 'brand × channel' },
      { code: 'csc',   fields: ['category','size','channel'],                      label: 'cat × size × channel' },
      { code: 'cc',    fields: ['category','channel'],                             label: 'cat × channel' },
    ];
    const $ = id => document.getElementById(id);

    function makeOption(item) {
      const opt = document.createElement('option');
      opt.value = item.value;
      opt.textContent = `${item.value}  (T:${item.n_tradera} V:${item.n_vinted})`;
      if (item.total === 0) {
        opt.classList.add('calc-no-data');
        opt.disabled = true;
      } else if (item.total < MIN_N) {
        opt.classList.add('calc-low-data');
      }
      return opt;
    }

    function fillSelect(selectEl, items, placeholderIfEmpty) {
      selectEl.innerHTML = '';
      if (!items || items.length === 0) {
        const opt = document.createElement('option');
        opt.value = '';
        opt.textContent = placeholderIfEmpty;
        opt.disabled = true;
        selectEl.appendChild(opt);
        return;
      }
      items.forEach(it => selectEl.appendChild(makeOption(it)));
    }

    function refreshCategories() {
      const brand = $('calc-brand').value;
      fillSelect($('calc-category'), cascade.cats_by_brand[brand], '— no categories for this brand —');
    }
    function refreshSizes() {
      const key = `${$('calc-brand').value}|${$('calc-category').value}`;
      fillSelect($('calc-size'), cascade.sizes_by_bc[key], '— no sizes for this brand × category —');
    }
    function refreshConditions() {
      const key = `${$('calc-brand').value}|${$('calc-category').value}|${$('calc-size').value || 'Unknown'}`;
      const conds = cascade.conds_by_bcs[key] || [];
      const sel = $('calc-condition');
      sel.innerHTML = '';
      const blank = document.createElement('option');
      blank.value = '';
      blank.textContent = 'Any (no condition filter)';
      sel.appendChild(blank);
      conds.forEach(it => sel.appendChild(makeOption(it)));
    }

    function predictForChannel(channel) {
      const cond = $('calc-condition').value;
      const inputs = {
        brand:    $('calc-brand').value,
        category: $('calc-category').value,
        size:     $('calc-size').value || 'Unknown',
        channel:  channel,
        condition: cond,
      };
      // Two-pass: prefer high-confidence (n ≥ MIN_N); fall back to any n.
      for (const [requiredN, conf] of [[MIN_N, 'high'], [1, 'low']]) {
        for (const lvl of LEVELS) {
          if (lvl.needsCondition && !cond) continue;
          const key = lvl.fields.map(f => inputs[f]).join('|');
          const e = lookups[lvl.code] && lookups[lvl.code][key];
          if (e && e.n >= requiredN) {
            return { ...e, label: lvl.label, code: lvl.code, confidence: conf };
          }
        }
      }
      return null;
    }

    function renderChannel(channel, result) {
      const box = document.querySelector(`.result-box[data-channel="${channel}"]`);
      box.classList.remove('empty', 'tradera', 'vinted', 'low-confidence');
      if (!result) {
        box.classList.add('empty');
        box.innerHTML = `
          <div class="channel-tag text-muted">${channel}</div>
          <div class="meta mt-2">No samples for this combination at any granularity.</div>`;
        return;
      }
      box.classList.add(channel);
      if (result.confidence === 'low') box.classList.add('low-confidence');
      const isFallback = result.code !== 'bcscZ' && result.code !== 'bcsc';
      const confidenceLabel = result.confidence === 'low' ? 'low conf.' : 'n ≥ 10';
      box.innerHTML = `
        <div class="confidence-badge ${result.confidence}">${confidenceLabel}</div>
        <div class="channel-tag">${channel}${channel === 'tradera' ? ' · realised' : ' · listed'}</div>
        <div class="d-flex align-items-baseline gap-2 mt-1">
          <div class="price">${result.median}<span class="unit"> kr</span></div>
          <div class="meta">range ${result.p25} – ${result.p75} kr · n=${result.n}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gran">Matched on ${result.label}${isFallback ? ' (fallback)' : ''}${result.confidence === 'low' ? ' · sample below n=10 threshold — treat as indicative' : ''}</div>`;
    }

    function predictBoth() {
      renderChannel('tradera', predictForChannel('tradera'));
      renderChannel('vinted',  predictForChannel('vinted'));
    }

    // Cascade wiring
    fillSelect($('calc-brand'), cascade.brands, '— no data —');
    refreshCategories();
    refreshSizes();
    refreshConditions();
    predictBoth();

    $('calc-brand').addEventListener('change', () => {
      refreshCategories(); refreshSizes(); refreshConditions(); predictBoth();
    });
    $('calc-category').addEventListener('change', () => {
      refreshSizes(); refreshConditions(); predictBoth();
    });
    $('calc-size').addEventListener('change', () => {
      refreshConditions(); predictBoth();
    });
    $('calc-condition').addEventListener('change', predictBoth);
  })();
  </script>

  <!-- ── Cross-Channel Comparison ── -->
  <div class="card mb-5 border-0 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-header bg-dark text-white d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between">
      <strong>Cross-Channel Comparison</strong>
      <span class="text-light" style="font-size:.8rem">
        Tradera realized vs Vinted asking · sorted by largest |Δ%|
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body p-0">
      <table class="table table-hover table-sm mb-0">
        <thead class="table-light">
          <tr>
            <th>Brand</th>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Tradera n</th>
            <th>Tradera median (kr)</th>
            <th>Vinted n</th>
            <th>Vinted median (kr)</th>
            <th>Δ kr</th>
            <th>Δ %</th>
            <th>Premium channel</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for r in cross_channel %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ r.brand }}</td>
            <td><small>{{ r.category }}</small></td>
            <td>{{ r.tradera_n }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.tradera_avg }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.vinted_n }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.vinted_avg }}</td>
            <td class="{% if r.delta_sek > 0 %}delta-positive{% else %}delta-negative{% endif %}">
              {{ r.delta_sek }}
            </td>
            <td class="{% if r.delta_pct > 0 %}delta-positive{% else %}delta-negative{% endif %}">
              {{ r.delta_pct }}%
            </td>
            <td><span class="channel-{{ r.premium_channel }}">{{ r.premium_channel }}</span></td>
          </tr>
          {% else %}
          <tr><td colspan="9" class="text-center text-muted py-3">No brand×category cells with both channels yet — add Vinted scrape coverage.</td></tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Top 20 Sourcing Picks (combined) ── -->
  <div class="card mb-5 border-0 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
      <strong>Top 20 Sourcing Picks</strong>
      <span class="ms-2 badge bg-light text-dark" style="font-weight:400">
        n ≥ 5 · ranked by realised value (n × median price), per channel
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body p-0">
      <table class="table table-hover table-sm mb-0">
        <thead class="table-light">
          <tr>
            <th>#</th><th>Channel</th><th>Brand</th><th>Category</th><th>Size</th>
            <th>n</th><th>Median (kr)</th><th>p25 – p75</th><th>Total (kSEK)</th>
            <th>Cycle time</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for cell in top_picks %}
          <tr>
            <td class="text-muted">{{ loop.index }}</td>
            <td><span class="channel-{{ cell.channel }}">{{ cell.channel }}</span></td>
            <td>{{ cell.brand }}</td>
            <td><small>{{ cell.category }}</small></td>
            <td>{{ cell.size }}</td>
            <td>{{ cell.n }}</td>
            <td>{% if cell.median_price_sek %}{{ cell.median_price_sek }}{% else %}–{% endif %}</td>
            <td>
              {% if cell.p25_sek and cell.p75_sek %}
                <small class="text-muted">{{ cell.p25_sek }} – {{ cell.p75_sek }}</small>
              {% else %}–{% endif %}
            </td>
            <td><span class="badge rounded-pill badge-{{ cell.velocity_class }}">{{ cell.velocity_score }}</span></td>
            <td>
              {% if cell.median_time_to_sell %}{{ cell.median_time_to_sell }} d{% else %}<small class="text-muted">–</small>{% endif %}
            </td>
          </tr>
          {% else %}
          <tr><td colspan="10" class="text-center text-muted py-3">No data yet.</td></tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Vinted Cycle-Time Insights ── -->
  <div class="card mb-5 border-0 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-header bg-secondary text-white d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between">
      <strong>Vinted Cycle-Time Insights</strong>
      <span class="text-light" style="font-size:.8rem">Items disappeared between runs → presumed sold</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body p-0">
      <table class="table table-sm mb-0">
        <thead class="table-light">
          <tr>
            <th>Brand</th><th>Category</th><th>Size</th><th>Sold (n)</th>
            <th>Avg days listed</th><th>Avg price (kr)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for r in cycle_time %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ r.brand }}</td>
            <td><small>{{ r.category }}</small></td>
            <td>{{ r.size }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.n_sold }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.avg_days }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.avg_price }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% else %}
          <tr><td colspan="6" class="text-center text-muted py-3">
            No cycle-time data yet — populates after items first scraped this week disappear from later weekly runs (need 2+ runs to start, 4+ weeks for confidence).
          </td></tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Full Analysis Table ── -->
  <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
    <div class="card-header">
      <strong>Full Analysis</strong>
      <span class="ms-2 text-muted" style="font-size:.8rem">All brand × category × size × channel cells</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <table id="full-table" class="table table-sm table-striped" style="width:100%">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Channel</th><th>Brand</th><th>Category</th><th>Size</th>
            <th>n</th><th>Median (kr)</th><th>p25</th><th>p75</th>
            <th>Total kSEK</th><th>Cycle (d)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for cell in all_cells %}
          <tr {% if cell.low_confidence %}class="text-muted"{% endif %}>
            <td><span class="channel-{{ cell.channel }}">{{ cell.channel }}</span></td>
            <td>{{ cell.brand }}</td>
            <td><small>{{ cell.category }}</small></td>
            <td>{{ cell.size }}</td>
            <td>{{ cell.n }}</td>
            <td>{% if cell.median_price_sek %}{{ cell.median_price_sek }}{% else %}–{% endif %}</td>
            <td>{% if cell.p25_sek %}{{ cell.p25_sek }}{% else %}–{% endif %}</td>
            <td>{% if cell.p75_sek %}{{ cell.p75_sek }}{% else %}–{% endif %}</td>
            <td><span class="badge rounded-pill {% if cell.low_confidence %}badge-dim{% else %}badge-{{ cell.velocity_class }}{% endif %}">{{ cell.velocity_score }}</span></td>
            <td>{% if cell.median_time_to_sell %}{{ cell.median_time_to_sell }}{% else %}<small class="text-muted">–</small>{% endif %}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-muted mt-4" style="font-size:.75rem">
    Tradera prices are <strong>realised</strong> sale prices (final auction bid). Vinted prices are <strong>asking</strong>
    prices on active listings (Vinted = fixed-price marketplace; asking ≈ transaction when an item sells).
    Cross-channel Δ% indicates expected price premium per side.
    Cycle time is inferred longitudinally — items present in one weekly run and absent in the next are treated as sold.
    Cells with n&lt;5 are low-confidence (greyed) and excluded from cross-channel comparisons and Top 20.
  </p>
</div>

<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.datatables.net/1.13.8/js/jquery.dataTables.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.datatables.net/1.13.8/js/dataTables.bootstrap5.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.datatables.net/buttons/2.4.2/js/dataTables.buttons.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.datatables.net/buttons/2.4.2/js/buttons.bootstrap5.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jszip/3.10.1/jszip.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.datatables.net/buttons/2.4.2/js/buttons.html5.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function () {
  $('#full-table').DataTable({
    pageLength: 50,
    order: [[8, 'desc']],
    dom: '<"d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-2"<"d-flex gap-2"Bf><l>>rtip',
    buttons: [{ extend: 'csvHtml5', text: 'Export CSV', className: 'btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary' }],
    columnDefs: [{ targets: [4,5,6,7,8,9], className: 'text-end' }]
  });
});
</script>
</body>
</html>
